<subSubSection pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1436,259,860]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,368,392]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" reason="1">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific name comes from the Latin word 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2010" box="[866,970,368,392]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Tmarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladiatus">
<emphasis box="[866,970,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">gladiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(sword-shaped), referring to the shape of the long RTA, adjective.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1436,259,860]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,439,464]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" reason="1">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Tang and Li, 2009" authorityName="Tang and Li" authorityYear="2009" box="[676,1020,439,464]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Tmarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="byssinus">
<emphasis box="[676,799,440,464]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">T. byssinus</emphasis>
Tang and 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, Z. X. &amp; Zhou, Y. F. &amp; Yang, Z. Z." box="[921,1020,439,463]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" pagination="65 - 66" refId="ref42926" refString="Li, Z. X., Zhou, Y. F. &amp; Yang, Z. Z. (2009) First description of the female of Stiphropus falciformus (Araneae: Thomisidae). Acta Arachnologica, Tokyo, 58, 65 - 66." type="journal article" year="2009">Li, 2009</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be separated from the latter by: 1) ITA sharp (stout in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang and Li" authorityYear="2009" box="[444,567,476,500]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Tmarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="byssinus">
<emphasis box="[444,567,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">T. byssinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 2) RTA long, sharp distally (short in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang and Li" authorityYear="2009" box="[1006,1129,476,500]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Tmarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="byssinus">
<emphasis box="[1006,1129,476,500]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">T. byssinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); 3) embolus equals 2 time the length of that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Tang and Li" authorityYear="2009" box="[376,498,512,536]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Tmarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="byssinus">
<emphasis box="[376,498,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">T. byssinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This new species can also be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName authority="Ono, 1977" authorityName="Ono" authorityYear="1977" box="[1054,1306,511,536]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Tmarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="taiwanus">
<emphasis box="[1054,1182,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">T. taiwanus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Ono, H." box="[1188,1306,511,535]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" pagination="61 - 84" refId="ref43056" refString="Ono, H. (1977) Thomisidae aus Japan I. Das Genus Tmarus Simon (Arachnida: Araneae). Acta Arachnologica, Tokyo, 27 (Spec. No.), 61 - 84." type="journal article" year="1977">Ono, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by absence of tegular apophysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="100" lastPageNumber="101" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1436,259,860]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,414,583,608]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis box="[199,344,583,608]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" reason="1">Description.</emphasis>
Male
</emphasis>
(
<typeStatus box="[429,529,583,607]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">holotype</typeStatus>
measured): Total length 3.40. Prosoma 1.45 long, 1.55 wide; opisthosoma 2.00 long, 1.00 wide. Dorsal shield of prosoma yellowish brown with grayish black marking. Eye tubercles grayish black. Eye measurements: AME 0.07; ALE 0.13; PME 0.08; PLE 0.12; AME–AME 0.13; AME–ALE 0.16; PME– PME 0.21; PME–PLE 0.28. MOA length 0.30 with front width 0.24 and back width 0.36. Chelicerae, gnathocoxae, labium and sternum yellow. Legs yellow; the distal of tibia, metatarsi and tarsi II dark brown; legs with spines; tibia and metatarsus II with 3, 4 pairs of ventral spines, respectively. Leg measurements: I: lost; II: 8.80 (2.60, 3.10, 2.10, 1.00); III: 3.95 (1.20, 1.60, 0.65, 0.50); IV: 3.90 (1.30, 1.40, 0.70, 0.50), leg formula: 234. Opisthosoma dorsally yellowish brown with reddish brown spots, venter yellow.
</paragraph>
<caption pageId="99" pageNumber="100" startId="99.[151,255,1955,1979]" targetBox="[158,1430,953,1931]" targetPageId="99">
<paragraph blockId="99.[151,1437,1955,2014]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,294,1955,1979]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">FIGURE 75.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Tang &amp; Li, 2010" authorityName="Tang &amp; Li" authorityYear="2010" box="[300,486,1956,1979]" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Tmarus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gladiatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[300,486,1956,1979]" italics="true" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">Tmarus gladiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[492,577,1955,1979]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[492,577,1955,1979]" pageId="99" pageNumber="100" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype from Xishuangbanna. A–B Palp (A Ventral, B Retrolateral). Scale bar: A–B = 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1435,151,391]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis box="[199,252,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Palp</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[267,414,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 74" captionStartId="98.[151,255,1956,1980]" captionTargetBox="[191,1396,159,1943]" captionTargetId="figure-47@98.[191,1396,159,1943]" captionTargetPageId="98" captionText="FIGURE 74. Tmarus gladiatus sp. nov., holotype from Xishuangbanna. A Habitus, dorsal; B–D Palp (B Prolateral, C Ventral, D Retrolateral). Scale bars: A = 1.0 mm; B–D = 0.1 mm." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">Figs 74 B–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[426,519,151,175]" captionStart="FIGURE 75" captionStartId="99.[151,255,1955,1979]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,953,1931]" captionTargetId="figure-303@99.[151,1436,950,1934]" captionTargetPageId="99" captionText="FIGURE 75. Tmarus gladiatus sp. nov., holotype from Xishuangbanna. A–B Palp (A Ventral, B Retrolateral). Scale bar: A–B = 0.1 mm." pageId="100" pageNumber="101">75 A–B</figureCitation>
). VTA short digitiform, ITA short, sharp, RTA long, distally sharp; embolus slen- der.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1435,151,391]" box="[199,418,223,248]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,293,224,248]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" reason="1">Female.</emphasis>
Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[199,545,259,284]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="100.[151,1435,151,391]" box="[199,545,259,284]" pageId="100" pageNumber="101">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,352,259,284]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="100" pageNumber="101" reason="1">Distribution.</emphasis>
